docs.abstract: Business, entertainment, news, activism and social connection will never be the same.
docs.snippet: Business, entertainment, news, activism and social connection will never be the same.
docs.lead_paragraph: It’s been well over two years since TikTok arrived in the United States in August 2018, offering a rejoinder to anyone who thought social media had lost its way. The app had everything: social commentary, comedy, crafting, memes, challenges, makeup tutorials and, of course, dances. Even those who weren’t totally sold on it couldn’t avoid the videos, which proliferated across platforms like Instagram, YouTube and Twitter.

headline.main: This Is Why You Heard About TikTok So Much in 2020
headline.print_headline: Why 2020 Was the Year That Belonged to TikTok
